Description: Easily manage wine and proton prefixes (Native Fork)
 Bottles lets you run Windows software on Linux, such as applications
 and games. It introduces a workflow that helps you organize by
 categorizing each software to your liking.
 .
 This is a native (non-Flatpak) version of Bottles.
 .
 Note: Bottle versioning (snapshots) requires the fvs2 binary from
 https://github.com/fvs-lab/fvs2 — it is not yet packaged for Debian/Ubuntu.
 The rest of Bottles works without it.
